description: In many fields of business, analysts must deal with data on many variables, for example; surveys with a large number of questions. In such cases, statistical tools known as multivariate methods must be used to analyse the data and drive business decisions.This unit covers such methods in three sections:   Cluster Analysis, Discriminant Analysis and MANOVA can be used to identify, predict and test for differences groups such as between distinct classes of customers or products;  Principal Components Analysis, Correspondence Analysis and Multidimensional Scaling are dimension reduction methods that help analysts to visualise complicated datasets; and finally, Factor Analysis and Structural Equation Modelling are used to predict and test theories and explain and predict business outcomes.
